4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Randolph County; to provide for a booking
10 fee to be assessed in certain cases; and to provide for the
11 distribution of the revenue from the fee.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
13 Section 1. (a) In Randolph County, the clerk of court
14 shall assess a booking fee of thirty dollars ($30) against
15 each defendant incarcerated in or booked in the Randolph
16 County Jail if the defendant is convicted of or pleads guilty
17 in cases prosecuted in the circuit or district court in the
18 county.
19 (b) The clerk of the court shall enter the booking fee
20 on the docket sheet and collect the fee in the same manner and
21 at the same time as other court costs are collected. The
22 booking fee assessed pursuant to this section shall be in
23 addition to all other fines, court costs, or other charges
24 provided by law. The court costs provided by this section
25 shall not be waived by any court unless all other fees,
26 assessments, costs, fines, and charges associated with the
27 case are waived.
28 (c) The clerk of court shall remit the booking fees
Page 1

(c) The clerk of court shall remit the booking fees
HB367 INTRODUCED
29 collected pursuant to this section on a monthly basis to the
30 Sheriff of Randolph County to be deposited in the Law
31 Enforcement Fund created pursuant to Section 45-56-232.01,
32 Code of Alabama 1975, and used for law enforcement purposes in
33 the county.
34 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
35 1, 2026.
